Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
readTransitionFile(25.10)                            readTransitionFile(25.10)

Name
       readTransitionFile  -  Reads external transition files that are used to
       perform maximum transition violation reporting and fixing

Syntax
       readTransitionFile

       -file <fileName>

       [-view <viewName>]

       Reads external transition files that are used to perform maximum  tran-
       sition violation reporting and fixing.

       The contents of a transition file must be in the following format:

       setTranTime [-add] [-maxR <slewValue> | -maxF <slewValue>] {<pinName>}

       or

       setTranTime [-add] [-minR <slewValue> | -minF <slewValue>] {<pinName>}

       Where:

              * -add: Specifies that the transition value is incremental.

              * -maxR | -maxF: Specifies the maximum rise or fall transition.

              * -minR | -minF: Specifies the minimum rise or fall transition.

                Note: The minimum transition values will be ignored while per-
                forming transition violation fixing.

              * <pinName>:  Specifies  the  pin  name for which the transition
                value is specified. To specify multiple pin names, you need to
                use separate setTranTime statements as given below:

                setTranTime -add -maxR 3.5 inst/A

                setTranTime -add -maxR 3.5 pinB

       Note: The readTransitionFile command uses the time unit that is written
       in the slew file. If time unit is specified as 1e-12, it reads the val-
       ues in picoseconds. For time unit specified as 1e-09, the command reads
       the values in nanoseconds. For example,

       # Time Unit : 1e-09 seconds

       setTranTime -minR 0.80050 {AAA/BBB/CCC/A}

       setTranTime -minF 0.580300 {AAA/BBB/DDD/A}

       When a transition file is read and third-party slew  values  are  anno-
       tated,  Innovus  uses the following command to report transition viola-
       tions with the annotated slews:

       timeDesign {-postRoute | -signoff | -reportOnly} -useTransitionFiles

Parameters
       -file <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the file that contains  information  about
              the transition time.

       -view <viewName>
              Specifies  the  view  name for which the transition file will be
              read in case of MMMC designs. You need to ensure that you  spec-
              ify  the transition files for all setup views to perform transi-
              tion violation fixing.  Note: This  parameter  is  required  for
              MMMC designs only.

Example
              * The following command reads an external transition file called
                sampleFile for non-MMMC designs:

                readTransitionFile -file sampleFile

              * The  following commands read view specific external transition
                files for a MMMC design:

                readTransitionFile -view view1 -file sampleFile1

                readTransitionFile -view view2 -file sampleFile2

